    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">QESCO Reference Number — Where is it on Your Bill?</h1>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-8 text-lg leading-relaxed">The QESCO reference number is printed in bold on the top-right section of your electricity bill. QESCO serves all 34 districts of Balochistan. This guide shows exactly where to find your reference number on any QESCO bill.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Where is the reference number on QESCO bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">The QESCO reference number is at the top-right section of your bill, labeled Ref. No. It is a 14-digit number above the barcode. QESCO covers Quetta, Gwadar, Turbat, Khuzdar, Hub, and all Balochistan districts.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">QESCO reference number format?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">The QESCO reference number is always 14 digits. No letters or dashes. Same every month. Example: 01234567890123. Used for online bill checking and payments through JazzCash, EasyPaisa, or bank apps.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">QESCO helpline for reference number?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Call QESCO helpline 081-9201445 or 118. Provide your CNIC and meter address. They will give you your reference number. QESCO also accepts queries via their Quetta head office on Brewery Road.</div></details>
    </div>

